 "Every option we can think of to treat these children, these unfortunate souls caught in webs not of their own weaving, is held up to the highest criteria:  that of modern medicine.  We are so fortunate these days, that we can understand the very nature of the cellular functions, the very heights of synaptic activity. And we will go on exploring, searching, until we have found the cure for every child. excerpt from Ms. Scratcherd's valedictorian speech*##higher##lower